    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now

      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;

    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

<div class="row gl-mt-3 js-search-settings-section">
<div class="col-lg-4 profile-settings-sidebar">
<h4 class="gl-mt-0">
Personal Access Tokens
</h4>
<p>
You can generate a personal access token for each application you use that needs access to the GitLab API.
</p>
<p>
You can also use personal access tokens to authenticate against Git over HTTP.
They are the only accepted password when you have Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) enabled.
</p>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-8">
<div data-testid="access-token-section" data-qa-selector="access_token_section"><!----> <!----></div>
<h5 class="gl-mt-0">
Add a personal access token
</h5>
<p class="profile-settings-content">
Enter the name of your application, and we'll return a unique personal access token.
</p>
<form class="js-requires-input" id="js-new-access-token-form" action="/-/profile/personal_access_tokens" accept-charset="UTF-8" data-remote="true" method="post">
<div class="row">
<div class="form-group col">
<div class="row">
<label class="label-bold col-md-12" for="personal_access_token_name">Token name</label>
<div class="col-md-6">
<input class="form-control gl-form-input" required="required" data-qa-selector="access_token_name_field" aria-describedby="access_token_help_text" type="text" name="personal_access_token[name]" id="personal_access_token_name">
</div>
<span class="form-text text-muted col-md-12" id="access_token_help_text">For example, the application using the token or the purpose of the token. Do not give sensitive information for the name of the token, as it will be visible to all project members.</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div class="col">
<div role="group" class="form-group gl-form-group" id="__BVID__27"><label for="personal_access_token_expires_at" class="d-block col-form-label" id="__BVID__27__BV_label_">
      Expiration date
      <!----> <!----></label><div class="bv-no-focus-ring"><div class="gl-datepicker d-inline-block gl-w-full gl-form-input-md" data-qa-selector="expiry_date_field"><div class="gl-relative"><input id="personal_access_token_expires_at" name="personal_access_token[expires_at]" type="text" placeholder="YYYY-MM-DD" autocomplete="off" class="gl-form-input gl-w-full form-control gl-pr-9!" data-testid="gl-datepicker-input" aria-label="Enter date" aria-describedby="__BVID__27__BV_description_"> <div class="gl-datepicker-actions"><button data-testid="clear-button" aria-label="Clear date" type="button" class="btn gl-pointer-events-auto btn-default btn-sm gl-button btn-default-tertiary btn-icon"><!----> <svg data-testid="clear-icon" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="gl-button-icon gl-icon s16"><use href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#clear"></use></svg>  <!----></button> <span data-testid="datepicker-calendar-icon" class="gl-px-2 gl-text-gray-500"><svg data-testid="calendar-icon" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="gl-display-block gl-icon s16"><use href="/assets/icons-ce4e8ebe16c824ec266af5c86cfa08b0d35e88b4fa857e862dd87bbc726986bc.svg#calendar"></use></svg></span></div></div><div class="pika-single gl-datepicker-theme position-absolute  is-hidden is-bound" style="position: static; left: auto; top: auto;"></div></div><!----><!----><small tabindex="-1" class="form-text text-gl-muted" id="__BVID__27__BV_description_"><!----></small></div></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<b aria-describedby="select_scope_help_text">
Select scopes
</b>
<p class="text-secondary" id="select_scope_help_text">
Scopes set the permission levels granted to the token.
<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/help/user/profile/personal_access_tokens.md#personal-access-token-scopes">Learn more.</a>
</p>
<fieldset>
<div class="gl-form-checkbox custom-control custom-checkbox">
<input id="personal_access_token_scopes_api" data-qa-selector="api_checkbox" class="custom-control-input" type="checkbox" value="api" name="personal_access_token[scopes][]">
<label data-qa-selector="api_label" class="custom-control-label" for="personal_access_token_scopes_api"><span>api</span><p class="help-text" data-testid="pajamas-component-help-text">Grants complete read/write access to the API, including all groups and projects, the container registry, and the package registry.</p></label>
</div>

<div class="gl-form-checkbox custom-control custom-checkbox">
<input id="personal_access_token_scopes_read_api" data-qa-selector="read_api_checkbox" class="custom-control-input" type="checkbox" value="read_api" name="personal_access_token[scopes][]">
<label data-qa-selector="read_api_label" class="custom-control-label" for="personal_access_token_scopes_read_api"><span>read_api</span><p class="help-text" data-testid="pajamas-component-help-text">Grants read access to the API, including all groups and projects, the container registry, and the package registry.</p></label>

if ('loading' in HTMLImageElement.prototype) {
  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

<h4 class="gl-mt-0">
Personal Access Tokens
</h4>
<p>
You can generate a personal access token for each application you use that needs access to the GitLab API.
</p>
<p>
You can also use personal access tokens to authenticate against Git over HTTP.
They are the only accepted password when you have Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) enabled.
</p>

</div>

<h4 class="gl-mt-0">
Personal Access Tokens
</h4>
<p>
You can generate a personal access token for each application you use that needs access to the GitLab API.
</p>
<p>
You can also use personal access tokens to authenticate against Git over HTTP.
They are the only accepted password when you have Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) enabled.
</p>

if ('loading' in HTMLImageElement.prototype) {
  document.querySelectorAll('img.lazy').forEach(img => {
    img.loading = 'lazy';
    let imgUrl = img.dataset.src;
    // Only adding width + height for avatars for now
    if (imgUrl.indexOf('/avatar/') > -1 && imgUrl.indexOf('?') === -1) {
      const targetWidth = img.getAttribute('width') || img.width;
      imgUrl += `?width=${targetWidth}`;
    }
    img.src = imgUrl;
    img.removeAttribute('data-src');
    img.classList.remove('lazy');
    img.classList.add('js-lazy-loaded');
    img.dataset.qa_selector = 'js_lazy_loaded_content';
  });
}

//]]>
</script>

<h4 class="gl-mt-0">
Personal Access Tokens
</h4>
<p>
You can generate a personal access token for each application you use that needs access to the GitLab API.
</p>
<p>
You can also use personal access tokens to authenticate against Git over HTTP.
They are the only accepted password when you have Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) enabled.
</p>
